The paper deals with interference alignment in wireless communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the practical implementation of the proposed scheme, which involves antenna arrays and channel estimation, making it relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) and communications (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper explores the robustness of the proposed technique to small channel estimation errors, which is a topic that falls under the computer engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
